'''Monique Deveaux''' is a Canadian philosopher and Professor and Canada Research Chair in Ethics and Global Social Change at the [[University of Guelph]]. She is known for her research on [[poverty]], [[cultural pluralism]] and [[global justice]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Weinstock |first1=Daniel M. |title=Book Reviews Monique Deveaux, . Cultural Pluralism and Dilemmas of Justice.Ithaca, N.Y.: Cornell University Press, 2000. Pp. xii+205. $35.00 (cloth). |journal=Ethics |date=October 2002 |volume=113 |issue=1 |pages=146â149 |doi=10.1086/340672 |url=https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/full/10.1086/340672 |accessdate=3 July 2018 |language=en |issn=0014-1704}}</ref>
